oops object orientated language

class is blue print of the real world entity which will define property(attributes) and behaviour(method)

object is the instance of class


class will give structure and design
while object bring that structure to life with specific data which is unique to that specific object
it is modular ,reusable ,scalable


constructor and its types

constructor which will initialize the object at time when it was initiated

constructor have same name as class name
automatically invoked when object is created

 1.Default constructor will initialize default values to the attribute

 2.Parameter constructor will initialize  values to the attribute which we will provide

 3.Copy constructor used other object to initialize a new object

 4.Private constructor restrict object creation from outside the class. It is commonly used in singleton design pattern

can a constructor be final,static, abstract

1. final it cannot be inherited so final is irrelevant
2. static constructor belong to object not the class
3. abstract constructor must be concrete so it must have its implementation

synchronized keyword in constructor not make sense as object level synchronization is not applicable before the object is fully created

can a constructor be inherited ?

no constructor are not inherited but a subclass can call the superclass constructor using super()

constructor have return statement but not a value

this keyword

1. differentiate b/w the instance variable and method,constructor parameter
2. constructor chaining
3. method chaining can be achieved by returning the current object
4. passing the current object in the function


disadvantages
this keyword don't work with static method as static method belong to class not to object and it will be having conflicting behavior

overuse can reduce clarity which cause confusion